 <sect2 id="sec.vmdp.step.win7.install">
  <title>Windows* 7 installation</title>
  <procedure>
   <step>
    <para>
     Boot the Windows* 7 installation CD-ROM, and a <guimenu>Select driver to be
     installed</guimenu> dialog will be displayed:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_select.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_select.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     Browse to the directory which contains the VMDP driver:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_from_cd.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_from_cd.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     Select the SUSE driver:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_suse_block_driver.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_install_windows_suse_block_driver.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>Then finish the installation of the Windows* 7.</para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     On first boot, go to the directory which contains the VMDP driver (this
     should be a CD-ROM as defined in virt-manager). The
     <command>VMDP-xxx.exe</command> needs to be copied from the CD (ISO) onto
     the hard disk and expanded. Then double-click the
    <command>Setup.exe</command> program.</para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     A pop-up window will appear, to confirm the action, click
     <guimenu>Yes</guimenu>:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_signed_driver.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_signed_driver.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     Accept the End User License Agreement:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_accept_eula.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_accept_eula.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     The program will install the SUSE Drivers for Windows* 7:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmpd_installation_in_progress.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmpd_installation_in_progress.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     Now you need to restart your computer:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_computer_restart.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_computer_restart.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     You can check using the Windows device manager that all drivers have been
     successfully installed:
    </para>
    <informalfigure pgwide="0">
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_driver_installed_device_manager.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="vmdp_driver_installed_device_manager.png" width="56%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </informalfigure>
   </step>
  </procedure>
 </sect2>
 
